22/05/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski and his Albanian counterpart, Fatos Nano, met in Ohrid on Wednesday (21 May).
They discussed bilateral issues, including joint efforts for speedier NATO integration in light of the US-Adriatic Charter, signed early this month by Macedonia, Albania, Croatia and the United States.
Crvenkovski and Nano agreed that their countries should intensify economic co-operation, especially implementation of the Free Trade Agreement.
The prime ministers also agreed to open a new border crossing at their next meeting in Debar.
(MIA - 21/05/03)
